First and foremost, thanks to all the people who went over this! Calibri Bold for designing the Decommissioned icon. To all the rest of you who helped in any way that I have forgotten about, please make yourselves known, or even PM me so that I can put you in the credits list.

Image found here.

Mythis.

Iclarity.


First, I wanted to use the Decommissioned class, but without any lolFoundation elements. I noticed that Decom. objects could be considered  and so I wondered what the difference between Decommissioned and Neutralized was in-universe. After some research and talking around, I concluded that Decommissioned objects were intentionally destroyed by the Foundation, while Neutralized ones were objects that were destroyed or deanomalized for any other reason.

Second, I noticed that almost all objects that were destroyed by the Foundation (save for previous Decom. items) were these massive, world-ending forces. I figured that there could conceivably be other reasons to destroy an object, though it would still be done very rarely. What about expense? Would the Foundation spend millions or even billions of dollars to contain an object, even if it had no use to them, and it could be destroyed fairly easily? Or how about legality? The Foundation is still subject to various laws imposed by the governments and entities supporting its existence, so what if the only way to contain an anomaly was in violation of those laws?











